article.headline: Lehigh 57, Army 52
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Zahir Carrington scored 16 points to lead Lehigh in a 57-52 win over Army Sunday. Marquis Hall contributed 11 points for Lehigh (8-9, 1-2 Patriot League). Army (8-9, 1-2 PL) led 31-22 at the half, in a game with four ties and three lead changes. Overcoming an early 15-point deficit, Lehigh took its first lead with 5:13 remaining, and then had to hold off Army in the closing seconds for its first league win of the season. Jarell Brown scored a game-high 17 points for Army. Lehigh shot 52 percent for the game, while holding the Black Knights to 42 percent shooting. Army shot just 33 percent in the second half, scoring 21 points in that time. Army outrebounded Lehigh 28-24. The Mountain Hawks were forced into 19 turnovers, but only five of them came in the second half.
